The paper deals with unsupervised domain mapping, which is a problem in computer vision. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and the focus on image transformation suggest that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new constraint for GANs, which is related to geometry and image structure, indicating that it could also be classified under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of unsupervised learning and the focus on constraints suggest that the paper could also be classified under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of quantitative and qualitative comparisons suggests that the paper could also be classified under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
